WEBVTT

00:03.699 --> 00:04.047
.

00:04.091 --> 00:07.007
[traffic roaring,
dog barking faintly]

00:11.185 --> 00:13.013
- You think there's a kid
in Kenny's crew

00:13.056 --> 00:14.231
that's over the age of 17?

00:14.275 --> 00:16.364
- More like 15.

00:17.234 --> 00:18.670
Yo, we got eyes

00:18.714 --> 00:20.933
on our boys on the block,
if y'all are ready.

00:20.977 --> 00:23.023
- Copy.
Shutting down now.

00:25.634 --> 00:27.418
- This one mine.

00:27.462 --> 00:28.854
Looking fine,

00:28.898 --> 00:30.117
as usual.

00:30.160 --> 00:31.205
- You know she's with me,
right?

00:31.248 --> 00:33.076
- Yeah, for now, son.
For now.

00:33.120 --> 00:34.251
- All right, all right.

00:34.295 --> 00:35.513
- All right,
so what you all need?

00:35.557 --> 00:36.688
The usual?

00:36.732 --> 00:37.863
- Actually, we need
a little extra today.

00:37.907 --> 00:39.082
We have friends up in Lakeview

00:39.126 --> 00:40.127
that had a taste
of the good stuff,

00:40.170 --> 00:41.650
want a little more.

00:45.436 --> 00:47.177
- How much extra weight
we talking?

00:47.221 --> 00:48.570
- 100 grams.

00:48.613 --> 00:50.267
- I don't usually carry
that much product on me,

00:50.311 --> 00:52.139
so I'ma need to do
a little wheelin' and dealin'.

00:52.182 --> 00:54.184
We talking straight packed
or powder?

00:54.228 --> 00:55.229
- Oh, packed up for sure.

00:55.272 --> 00:56.795
- Okay, I can make that happen.

00:56.839 --> 00:58.101
Meet me at Division Street,

00:58.145 --> 01:00.364
One Stop parking lot,
at 4:00 p.m.

01:00.408 --> 01:02.018
- All right.
- We can make that happen.

01:02.062 --> 01:04.238
- And look, feel free
to come solo, baby.

01:04.281 --> 01:05.630
- Hey, I heard that.

01:05.674 --> 01:07.023
Yeah, it was meant
for you to hear.

01:07.067 --> 01:08.155
- Watch yourself.

01:08.198 --> 01:10.722
We'll see you later.

01:10.766 --> 01:12.724
- All right,
kid took the bait.

01:15.597 --> 01:18.774
- Downside to using
child labor:

01:18.817 --> 01:20.732
inexperienced.

01:20.776 --> 01:26.695
♪

01:26.738 --> 01:28.610
- It's 5:00.

01:28.653 --> 01:30.002
- For a dealer,
being an hour late

01:30.046 --> 01:32.092
is actually considered early.

01:33.789 --> 01:36.270
- Nothing so far.

01:36.313 --> 01:38.489
- Should've had Upton
do the deal alone.

01:38.533 --> 01:39.925
Kid's got eyes for her.

01:41.536 --> 01:42.928
- Units in 21,
we're getting multiple calls

01:42.972 --> 01:45.975
of shots fired
at 3852 South on Wells.

01:47.150 --> 01:48.499
We just got a call
over the zone.

01:48.543 --> 01:51.023
Shots fired two blocks away.
We're gonna take it.

01:54.679 --> 01:57.421
♪

01:57.465 --> 01:59.162
This is the site here.

01:59.206 --> 02:05.212
♪

02:05.255 --> 02:06.387
How we look, Ruz?

02:06.430 --> 02:08.911
- We're good.
We're good.

02:08.954 --> 02:16.136
♪

02:17.224 --> 02:18.268
- Body.

02:18.312 --> 02:21.793
♪

02:21.837 --> 02:23.143
Hold on.
Call it in!

02:23.186 --> 02:25.014
- 5021 Ida.
Roll an ambulance.

02:25.057 --> 02:27.016
- Hang on, bro.
Okay?

02:27.059 --> 02:28.844
Hang on. Help is coming.

02:28.887 --> 02:31.803
Malik.
Malik!

02:31.847 --> 02:36.025
♪

02:36.068 --> 02:37.418
Malik!

02:40.682 --> 02:43.511
♪

02:43.554 --> 02:45.904
Ain't got a pulse.
He's gone.

02:45.948 --> 02:52.433
♪

02:52.476 --> 02:54.870
Just a dumb kid, man.

02:58.439 --> 02:59.701
♪

03:00.223 --> 03:01.833
- Kid took two to the chest.

03:01.877 --> 03:04.532
Found two nine-millimeter
rounds right next to the body.

03:06.098 --> 03:07.665
- No, just took two and dropped
right where he stood.

03:07.709 --> 03:10.015
- Nothing recovered so far.

03:10.059 --> 03:11.887
- Been doing surveillance
on this block for weeks.

03:11.930 --> 03:14.194
This is a known re-up spot
for Kenny's corner boys.

03:14.237 --> 03:15.934
- DOA was actually a kid
we were supposed

03:15.978 --> 03:17.414
to meet up with tonight.

03:17.458 --> 03:18.937
- All right, so the kid
asks for more weight.

03:18.981 --> 03:20.896
Kenny gets spooked that
he might be snitching,

03:20.939 --> 03:22.158
so he shoots him.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.377
- We have two witnesses
that saw a boy

03:23.420 --> 03:24.769
running away from
the construction site

03:24.813 --> 03:26.075
moments after the shots
were fired.

03:26.118 --> 03:27.250
- And the physical
description

03:27.294 --> 03:28.338
matches Nathan,
Malik's sidekick.

03:28.382 --> 03:29.818
- Well, maybe he's
the shooter.

03:29.861 --> 03:31.820
- Or he's a friend
that saw the shooter

03:31.863 --> 03:33.038
and he ran like hell.

03:33.082 --> 03:34.257
- Well, either way,
he's our only lead,

03:34.301 --> 03:35.737
so let's find him fast.

03:39.393 --> 03:41.133
- Nathan Hawkins, 15 years old.

03:41.177 --> 03:42.526
Dropped out of school
a year ago

03:42.570 --> 03:44.267
to start slinging dope
for Kenny Armstrong.

03:44.311 --> 03:45.703
- Yeah, he has one arrest
on his record.

03:45.747 --> 03:47.227
It's for a delivery charge
three months ago.

03:47.270 --> 03:48.924
- Any idea where he might
be hanging out?

03:48.967 --> 03:51.056
- His last known address was
his mom's apartment in Austin.

03:51.100 --> 03:53.668
But she OD'd a year ago around
the time he started dealing.

03:54.930 --> 03:56.540
- Uh, been behind bars
for the last decade.

03:56.584 --> 03:58.063
- Who bailed him out
when he got busted?

03:58.107 --> 03:59.456
- That would be
Sarah Washington,

03:59.500 --> 04:01.197
Nathan's aunt.
- All right,

04:01.241 --> 04:02.807
so find an address.
Check it out.

04:10.859 --> 04:13.253
♪

04:13.296 --> 04:14.645
Hey, Dr. Appelbaum.

04:14.689 --> 04:16.256
Thanks for getting back to me
so quickly.

04:16.299 --> 04:19.694
Look, uh, I was hoping
you could call me in a refill.

04:19.737 --> 04:22.566
I ran out, and my shoulder's
still killing me.

04:23.959 --> 04:25.090
What?

04:25.134 --> 04:26.266
Eight days?

04:26.309 --> 04:27.658
No, no, no, no, no.

04:27.702 --> 04:29.660
That's not gonna work.
I need more tonight.

04:34.143 --> 04:36.101
I'm Officer Atwater.

04:36.145 --> 04:37.494
This is Officer Ruzek.

04:37.538 --> 04:39.322
Are you Sarah Washington?

04:40.628 --> 04:42.282
- We're looking
for your nephew,

04:42.325 --> 04:44.022
Nathan Hawkins.
Does he live here?

04:44.066 --> 04:45.763
- He does, but he's not home.

04:45.807 --> 04:47.896
- When was the last time
you saw him?

04:47.939 --> 04:49.550
- This morning.

04:49.593 --> 04:52.117
- Okay, would you mind if we
took a look around his room?

04:54.685 --> 04:56.861
Y'all got five minutes.

04:56.905 --> 04:58.036
- Yes, ma'am.

04:58.080 --> 04:59.473
- Down the hall.

04:59.516 --> 05:01.475
In the back.

05:09.961 --> 05:11.311
- Man, dude.

05:12.529 --> 05:13.574
Look at this place.

05:13.617 --> 05:14.792
No wonder kids like Nathan

05:14.836 --> 05:17.012
end up working for guys
like Kenny.

05:17.055 --> 05:19.667
- Mom's dead, dad locked up.

05:19.710 --> 05:21.146
Working those corners
is probably

05:21.190 --> 05:23.323
the most stable thing
in that boy's life.

05:25.673 --> 05:28.066
- Ah, there's a POD camera
across the street.

05:29.459 --> 05:30.982
Maybe something from that,
yeah?

05:34.769 --> 05:36.379
- Okay, there's Nathan.

05:36.423 --> 05:38.381
- All right, so that's
time-stamped 5:45,

05:38.425 --> 05:40.078
45 minutes after
Malik was killed.

05:40.122 --> 05:42.385
Let's keep going.
- Okay.

05:44.518 --> 05:46.084
- Freeze right there.

05:46.128 --> 05:47.651
There's Nathan right there.
Passenger side window.

05:47.695 --> 05:50.045
- Yeah.
Who's she?

05:52.047 --> 05:55.442
Okay, bro, let's see if we can
get facial rec on the driver.

06:05.713 --> 06:07.671
Check around back?
- Yeah.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.547
- Back the hell up now!

06:13.590 --> 06:14.896
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!
- Hey, hey!

06:14.939 --> 06:16.506
What are you doing?
- Yo, we're CPD.

06:16.550 --> 06:18.203
We're CPD.
- Put that gun down.

06:18.247 --> 06:19.466
- Let me see your badge.

06:19.509 --> 06:20.815
- Okay, I'll show you
the badge,

06:20.858 --> 06:22.338
but I need you to put
that gun down.

06:22.382 --> 06:23.557
- I will when you show me
your badge.

06:23.600 --> 06:25.602
- There it is right there.
You see that?

06:25.646 --> 06:27.038
We are cops, okay?

06:27.082 --> 06:29.432
Put the gun down.

06:30.390 --> 06:31.478
- Now, you leave
that gun inside.

06:31.521 --> 06:33.044
You meet us out front.

06:33.088 --> 06:34.219
All right?
Right now.

06:34.263 --> 06:35.743
- Yeah.

06:37.919 --> 06:39.355
- Get your hands
out of your pockets

06:39.399 --> 06:40.878
and come here.

06:40.922 --> 06:42.532
Come right here.

06:42.576 --> 06:44.229
Keep 'em up.

06:46.014 --> 06:48.059
What the hell is wrong
with you?

06:48.103 --> 06:50.584
♪

06:50.627 --> 06:52.063
Pull a gun on the cops?

06:52.107 --> 06:53.630
- Well, how the hell
was I supposed to know?

06:53.674 --> 06:55.066
It's not like you sent
a résumé ahead of time.

06:55.110 --> 06:57.155
All I saw was two dudes
walking up on my house.

06:57.199 --> 06:58.374
Is this necessary?

06:58.418 --> 07:00.202
- Yeah, you just
pulled a gun on us.

07:00.245 --> 07:01.812
All right?

07:02.596 --> 07:03.945
Is it registered?

07:03.988 --> 07:05.903
- It sure is, and I can
show you the permit.

07:05.947 --> 07:09.733
- Okay. Do you know anybody
by the name of Nathan Hawkins?

07:09.777 --> 07:10.821
- Yeah.

07:10.865 --> 07:12.780
- When was the last time
you saw him?

07:13.650 --> 07:15.304
- I don't know.
Two, three weeks ago.

07:15.347 --> 07:16.653
- Wrong answer.

07:16.697 --> 07:17.915
- Next wrong answer,
we're gonna bring you in,

07:17.959 --> 07:19.439
and we're gonna start
writing up paper.

07:19.482 --> 07:20.614
- Last chance, Laila.

07:20.657 --> 07:21.832
♪

07:21.876 --> 07:23.486
- Why the hell
do you know my name?

07:23.530 --> 07:25.749
- Because you are a suspect
in a murder investigation.

07:25.793 --> 07:26.968
That's why we know your name.

07:27.011 --> 07:28.578
- What the hell are you
talking about?

07:28.622 --> 07:30.058
- We're talking about
how we have a video

07:30.101 --> 07:31.625
of you and Nathan Hawkins
riding in your car--

07:31.668 --> 07:34.018
this car--this afternoon.

07:34.062 --> 07:36.760
- No, I think you got
the wrong person.

07:36.804 --> 07:38.501
- I think we should
bring her in.

07:38.545 --> 07:40.024
What'd I do?

07:41.243 --> 07:42.549
You helped your friend
Kenny Armstrong

07:42.592 --> 07:43.680
kill Nathan Hawkins.

07:45.813 --> 07:47.510
- Then prove us wrong, Laila.
Where is he?

07:47.554 --> 07:50.165
- He's right here.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.471
- Nathan.
- You guys got it

07:51.514 --> 07:52.863
all wrong, all right?

07:52.907 --> 07:54.561
Laila's not trying
to kill me, all right?

07:54.604 --> 07:55.605
She's trying to help me.

07:55.649 --> 08:00.654
♪

08:04.135 --> 08:04.309
.

08:04.353 --> 08:06.181
- Man, I ain't saying nothing
to y'all.

08:07.443 --> 08:08.923
Come on, man,
what happened?

08:08.966 --> 08:10.315
You and Malik,
you get into an argument?

08:10.359 --> 08:11.534
He steal from you?
He screw your girlfriend?

08:11.578 --> 08:12.709
What?
- Man, not even close.

08:12.753 --> 08:15.103
Okay? Malik was my boy.

08:15.146 --> 08:17.453
All right?
We were tight.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.281
I'd never hurt him, man.
Never.

08:19.324 --> 08:21.457
- Okay, you didn't do it.

08:21.501 --> 08:22.676
Who did, Nathan?

08:25.766 --> 08:27.115
- Don't know.

08:27.158 --> 08:30.466
- Look, we all know what's
going on here, okay?

08:30.510 --> 08:33.164
We know that Malik asked Kenny
for some more weight.

08:33.208 --> 08:34.775
So Kenny thought that Malik
was snitching,

08:34.818 --> 08:35.776
so he killed him.

08:35.819 --> 08:37.429
- He thinks you are too.

08:37.473 --> 08:39.736
Right?
Thinks you're snitching?

08:39.780 --> 08:41.782
- But I'm not.

08:41.825 --> 08:43.348
Malik wouldn't either.

08:43.392 --> 08:44.741
- Doesn't matter,
if Kenny thinks you are.

08:44.785 --> 08:46.787
- Kenny thinks you are,
he's gonna kill you too.

08:49.616 --> 08:52.140
- Look, Nathan.

08:52.183 --> 08:53.576
Look at me for a second.

08:53.620 --> 08:56.274
That's why you went
to Laila's, right?

08:56.318 --> 08:57.537
That's why you went
to Laila's.

08:57.580 --> 08:59.190
You were looking
for a place to hide out.

08:59.234 --> 09:01.105
Look, bro, we just need
your help.

09:01.149 --> 09:02.803
Okay, we don't care
that you sell drugs.

09:02.846 --> 09:04.805
We don't care, bro.
Not at all.

09:04.848 --> 09:06.937
We just need to know if you saw
who did the murder.

09:06.981 --> 09:08.243
That's all.
- I didn't.

09:08.286 --> 09:09.592
- Don't lie to me.
- Man, I'm not.

09:09.636 --> 09:11.986
♪

09:12.029 --> 09:13.422
- Did Nathan see
who shot Malik?

09:13.465 --> 09:15.511
- No, but he knows
it was Kenny.

09:15.555 --> 09:18.166
Hell, my five-year-old niece
knows it's Kenny.

09:18.209 --> 09:19.646
- Okay, so let me
get this straight.

09:19.689 --> 09:21.648
You run with Kenny Armstrong,
but at the same time,

09:21.691 --> 09:23.519
you protect kids
from getting shot by him?

09:23.563 --> 09:27.262
- I don't run with Kenny
or anybody else.

09:27.305 --> 09:29.177
Now, we used to be a thing,

09:29.220 --> 09:32.528
but I've been out the game
for nine years.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.269
I haven't gotten as much
as a parking ticket.

09:34.312 --> 09:35.792
So don't lump me up
with Kenny

09:35.836 --> 09:39.100
or any other punk-ass
gangbanger I grew up with.

09:41.319 --> 09:43.757
- I grew up.
That's why.

09:43.800 --> 09:46.542
♪

09:46.586 --> 09:49.240
We all make mistakes
when we're young.

09:50.720 --> 09:52.287
Even you, Detective.

09:52.330 --> 09:56.683
♪

09:56.726 --> 09:58.075
- She's a tough chick.

09:58.119 --> 09:59.381
- Yeah.
Smart too.

09:59.424 --> 10:01.078
Nathan's lucky to have her
in his life.

10:01.122 --> 10:02.776
- Yeah, we'll see about that.

10:02.819 --> 10:05.039
Come on, Kev.
You and me.

10:05.082 --> 10:06.997
- Come on.

10:07.041 --> 10:11.698
♪

10:11.741 --> 10:13.525
All right, Ms. Davis.
You're free to go.

10:13.569 --> 10:16.224
- Okay, good.
Now, what about Nathan?

10:16.267 --> 10:18.443
Can I take him home too?

10:18.487 --> 10:20.663
We're charging him
with heroin distribution.

10:20.707 --> 10:22.317
Heroin distribution

10:22.360 --> 10:24.232
for slinging dime bags
on the corner?

10:24.275 --> 10:27.148
- Well, if he agrees to
cooperate in the murder case,

10:27.191 --> 10:28.802
we might be able
to cut him a break.

10:28.845 --> 10:30.281
- But he didn't see anything.

10:30.325 --> 10:33.197
- Well, that doesn't mean
he can't wear a wire.

10:33.241 --> 10:34.764
- That boy has a target
on his back

10:34.808 --> 10:36.592
the size of Soldier Field
and you want him

10:36.636 --> 10:38.246
to wear a wire?

10:38.289 --> 10:41.553
Kenny will kill his ass
in ten seconds flat.

10:41.597 --> 10:43.947
- Well, God doesn't give
with both hands.

10:43.991 --> 10:45.470
- Nathan is a good boy.

10:45.514 --> 10:48.604
He is a scared-ass little kid
with no place to go,

10:48.648 --> 10:50.345
and it is your job
to help him.

10:50.388 --> 10:53.478
- Listen, it's my job
to arrest

10:53.522 --> 10:55.176
Malik's killer,
Kenny Armstrong,

10:55.219 --> 10:56.830
your ex-boyfriend.

10:56.873 --> 10:59.963
Right now, Nathan is my
best shot at doing that.

11:00.007 --> 11:01.312
- Introduce me to Kenny.

11:03.488 --> 11:04.576
Right?

11:04.620 --> 11:05.839
We know his crew
meets at his crib.

11:05.882 --> 11:07.405
Find a way to get me in there.

11:08.319 --> 11:10.234
So I can plant the wire.

11:17.677 --> 11:20.897
Okay, then you gotta promise me
that you're gonna get Nathan

11:20.941 --> 11:23.247
out of Chicago fast.

11:24.553 --> 11:26.163
- Deal.

11:32.909 --> 11:34.737
- I got you, man.

11:34.781 --> 11:36.521
All right.

11:36.565 --> 11:38.828
- You ain't gonna be here
too long.

11:38.872 --> 11:40.351
Long as it takes for us
to find somebody

11:40.395 --> 11:42.179
to take you in.

11:43.746 --> 11:46.053
You got anybody we can
reach out to outside the state?

11:46.096 --> 11:47.707
Anywhere you wanna go?

11:49.230 --> 11:51.319
- No, I'm not interested
in leaving.

11:52.146 --> 11:54.278
- Hey, come on, man.
I dig it.

11:56.019 --> 11:58.065
Listen, man, I get it.

11:58.108 --> 12:00.937
Moving is rough, but you might
actually like a new city.

12:01.938 --> 12:03.897
My little brother
had to relocate to Texas.

12:03.940 --> 12:06.073
He wasn't feeling it at first.

12:06.116 --> 12:07.509
Digs it now.

12:09.903 --> 12:11.731
- My cousin.

12:12.862 --> 12:15.343
He's older.
He lives in Atlanta.

12:15.386 --> 12:16.561
I ain't seen him in a while,

12:16.605 --> 12:17.998
but he's always been nice
to me.

12:18.041 --> 12:19.347
- Okay.

12:19.390 --> 12:21.479
Track cuz down.

12:21.523 --> 12:23.351
All right.
- Thanks.

12:24.918 --> 12:27.181
Yo, you leavin'?

12:27.224 --> 12:30.053
- Yeah, man, I gotta get
to a birthday party.

12:30.097 --> 12:31.402
But you're all set.

12:31.446 --> 12:34.014
We got a police officer
at the door.

12:34.057 --> 12:36.190
They got you.

12:36.233 --> 12:37.844
You're good.

12:43.850 --> 12:47.027
♪

12:49.159 --> 12:51.031
- I'm cool.
Good.

12:51.074 --> 12:52.380
So what's this,
a first date?

12:53.729 --> 12:55.600
To a 60-year-old's
birthday party?

12:55.644 --> 12:57.385
No, I don't think so.

12:57.428 --> 13:00.127
- Okay, a few months, then.

13:02.042 --> 13:04.305
[Glenn Jones' "We've Only
Just Begun" playing on stereo]

13:04.348 --> 13:07.699
- ♪ Let me show you

13:07.743 --> 13:10.485
♪ We've only just begun

13:10.528 --> 13:13.488
♪ The romance is not over

13:13.531 --> 13:16.578
♪ Gotta a lot, a lot
of love to give ♪

13:16.621 --> 13:18.536
- Surprise.
- Surprise.

13:18.580 --> 13:20.582
- ♪ We've only just begun

13:20.625 --> 13:24.412
- Laila, good to see you, baby.

13:24.455 --> 13:27.241
So glad you're here
to help me celebrate.

13:27.284 --> 13:29.330
- Look at you, girl.

13:29.373 --> 13:31.071
Damn, just as beautiful
as ever.

13:31.114 --> 13:32.550
- Hey, Kenny.

13:32.594 --> 13:34.422
- Thanks for coming.
- Yeah.

13:34.465 --> 13:36.076
- You know Mama always
liked you more than me.

13:36.119 --> 13:37.904
- Yeah.
Hey, y'all.

13:37.947 --> 13:39.601
This is my friend Keith.

13:39.644 --> 13:41.777
- ♪ Passions run wild

13:41.821 --> 13:44.911
♪ And love the night

13:46.869 --> 13:48.305
- Nothing much.

13:48.349 --> 13:51.613
- Make sure y'all go and get
some of that pork, you know?

13:51.656 --> 13:53.354
I brought it in from St. Louis.

13:53.397 --> 13:55.573
- I actually like
how that cobbler looks.

13:55.617 --> 13:56.879
- Best peach cobbler
in the city.

13:56.923 --> 13:58.141
- You kidding.

13:58.185 --> 13:59.795
- Better get inside
before it's all gone.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.623
- Okay, I can do that.
You need anything?

14:01.666 --> 14:03.059
- Mm-mm.
- All right.

14:03.103 --> 14:04.800
Happy birthday, Mama.
- Thank you, baby.

14:04.844 --> 14:08.325
- ♪ Much more that we can do

14:46.973 --> 14:48.844
- Pretty good.
Found Kenny's man cave.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.890
Seems like a good place
to do some talking.

14:55.198 --> 14:56.721
Okay.

15:01.770 --> 15:03.250
- Wait. I'll be right back.

15:03.293 --> 15:04.860
- Cool.
- All right.

15:04.904 --> 15:06.993
♪

15:07.036 --> 15:09.038
- Hey.

15:09.082 --> 15:11.606
It's been a while, Laila.

15:11.649 --> 15:14.304
Thought you were trying
to avoid me.

15:14.348 --> 15:15.653
- Just been busy,

15:15.697 --> 15:17.699
you know, down at the center.

15:17.742 --> 15:19.614
- Yeah, I heard about that.

15:19.657 --> 15:21.355
Yeah, you working
with the kids, right?

15:21.398 --> 15:22.704
- Mm-hmm.

15:22.747 --> 15:24.880
- You know, I got a lot
of respect for that.

15:24.924 --> 15:28.449
How 'bout I make a donation
to the cause, you know?

15:28.492 --> 15:31.365
- No.
No, I'm cool.

15:32.409 --> 15:33.715
- No offense.

15:33.758 --> 15:36.152
I just wanna keep
this thing legit.

15:36.196 --> 15:37.371
- Yeah, the choice is yours.

15:37.414 --> 15:39.851
- But thanks for offering.

15:39.895 --> 15:41.984
- Hey, yo, Marlo.
- Yo.

15:43.638 --> 15:45.596
- Yo, keep these fools
out of my basement.

15:45.640 --> 15:46.902
- Yeah, all right.

15:46.946 --> 15:48.425
- Mama, I'm gonna grab a drink.

15:48.469 --> 15:49.644
Can I get you something?

15:49.687 --> 15:51.385
- I'm good, sweetie.
- Okay.

15:51.428 --> 15:55.128
♪

15:58.827 --> 16:01.003
- Okay, let me know
when you got a visual.

16:01.047 --> 16:02.744
- We've got eyes.

16:04.964 --> 16:11.971
♪

16:15.626 --> 16:17.802
- Hey, uh...

16:17.846 --> 16:19.369
let's not get worked up, okay?

16:21.067 --> 16:22.590
- I got lost.

16:22.633 --> 16:23.808
- Let me get back to the party.

16:25.462 --> 16:29.814
♪

16:33.122 --> 16:33.296
.

16:33.340 --> 16:35.211
- All right.
Come on, fellas.

16:35.255 --> 16:36.604
There's no need to play
with guns, okay?

16:36.647 --> 16:38.214
- I said, what you doing
down here?

16:38.258 --> 16:39.607
- I told you, I was looking
around and I got lost, okay?

16:39.650 --> 16:44.220
- Nah, bro.
You see, I just met you.

16:46.005 --> 16:48.659
And the way I see things, man,
that just don't feel right.

16:49.486 --> 16:51.053
- We gotta get in there now.
- Okay, wait. Give him a sec.

16:51.097 --> 16:52.533
He still hasn't used
the safe word.

16:52.576 --> 16:54.274
- I understand that, Kenny.
Okay?

16:54.317 --> 16:55.797
I should have asked
your permission first.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.973
I didn't mean
no disrespect, man.

16:58.017 --> 17:00.889
- Yeah, you should've.

17:00.932 --> 17:04.371
So I'ma ask you
one more time.

17:04.414 --> 17:05.676
Why you down here, Keith?

17:07.983 --> 17:11.856
- Laila told me about
your '96 ball, man.

17:11.900 --> 17:14.598
'96 Bulls, come on, that's
my favorite team of all time.

17:14.642 --> 17:15.947
I had--

17:15.991 --> 17:17.601
- Yeah.

17:17.645 --> 17:19.429
- Down here talking to Kenny.
That's all.

17:20.865 --> 17:22.215
Why's he got a gun
in his hand?

17:22.258 --> 17:23.825
- We're here chatting
with your new man.

17:23.868 --> 17:25.261
- Put the gun away
before you hurt someone.

17:25.305 --> 17:26.958
- Hey, listen. It's okay, baby.
- Hey.

17:27.002 --> 17:28.395
- It was just a
misunderstanding, that's all.

17:28.438 --> 17:29.961
I should have asked
for permission first.

17:32.225 --> 17:35.010
- Check out his '96 ball.

17:35.054 --> 17:36.925
- You left a party
to come look at that crap?

17:36.968 --> 17:39.493
You crazy?

17:39.536 --> 17:41.277
I knew I shouldn't have
told you about this ball.

17:41.321 --> 17:42.539
Come on, let's go get--
- No, no, no, no, not yet.

17:44.063 --> 17:45.977
- You ain't never
been down here before.

17:46.021 --> 17:48.676
And I just got that ball
last week.

17:48.719 --> 17:51.592
Which means the two of y'all
are lying about something.

17:51.635 --> 17:53.202
♪

17:53.246 --> 17:55.726
How you know about this,
Laila?

17:58.555 --> 17:59.774
Your mama.

17:59.817 --> 18:01.297
♪

18:01.341 --> 18:03.430
She always joking about
how stupid you are

18:03.473 --> 18:05.736
spending all your money
on this nonsense.

18:05.780 --> 18:07.695
♪

18:07.738 --> 18:09.349
Go ask her.

18:09.392 --> 18:11.873
♪

18:11.916 --> 18:13.353
Come on, let's go ask her.

18:13.396 --> 18:15.006
Let's go ruin her party...
- No, no.

18:15.050 --> 18:16.138
- About this crap.

18:16.182 --> 18:18.445
- Not yet.
Not yet.

18:18.488 --> 18:20.490
Yeah.

18:20.534 --> 18:22.318
♪

18:22.362 --> 18:24.015
I'm sorry.

18:24.059 --> 18:26.061
It's just a big
misunderstanding, you know?

18:26.105 --> 18:28.281
♪

18:28.324 --> 18:30.631
Hey, go on.
Get out of here.

18:30.674 --> 18:32.763
Go enjoy the party.

18:32.807 --> 18:39.988
♪

18:43.339 --> 18:44.688
- Hey.

18:44.732 --> 18:46.299
You're good to go.

18:46.342 --> 18:49.693
Thank you, and appreciate you
for helping me out back there.

18:49.737 --> 18:50.999
It means a lot.

18:51.042 --> 18:52.435
- Sure thing.
- No, seriously.

18:52.479 --> 18:54.089
If that charity thing
doesn't work out for you,

18:54.133 --> 18:55.612
you should think about
a future here.

18:55.656 --> 18:59.181
Let's not get carried away.

18:59.225 --> 19:02.576
- Okay, I understand.
But real quick.

19:02.619 --> 19:05.056
We were rapping with Nathan's
cousin down in Atlanta,

19:05.100 --> 19:06.493
and he's got two kids.

19:06.536 --> 19:07.885
He's a little worried
that Nathan's problems

19:07.929 --> 19:09.452
are gonna follow him
down there.

19:09.496 --> 19:12.151
So do you know of any other
family that Nathan has

19:12.194 --> 19:14.240
outside of Chicago
we can send that boy to?

19:14.283 --> 19:16.851
- Um...

19:16.894 --> 19:19.723
he's got a grandma
down in New Orleans.

19:19.767 --> 19:22.204
- Grandma in New Orleans.
We will track her down.

19:22.248 --> 19:23.945
We're gonna do everything
in our power to make sure

19:23.988 --> 19:25.555
that Nathan gets out of here,
okay?

19:25.599 --> 19:27.383
You got my word on that.

19:27.427 --> 19:29.037
- If you say so.

19:30.430 --> 19:32.562
You don't

19:32.606 --> 19:34.825
- I don't trust anybody,

19:34.869 --> 19:36.827
let alone a smooth-talking cop.

19:36.871 --> 19:39.308
- Well, you obviously
don't know me too well.

19:39.352 --> 19:41.223
- You're right.
I don't.

19:43.051 --> 19:44.226
So why don't you
buy me a drink

19:44.270 --> 19:45.575
and let me know
who you really are?

19:49.753 --> 19:51.755
- Okay, here we go.

19:51.799 --> 19:55.368
Glass of water.
Shot of Hennessy.

19:55.411 --> 19:57.718
I see you into that
hard stuff, huh?

19:57.761 --> 20:00.938
- I'm not wasting calories
on that fruity crap.

20:00.982 --> 20:03.637
Or a Heineken.

20:03.680 --> 20:04.768
- Straight up,
you've been

20:04.812 --> 20:06.117
around them
white boys too long.

20:06.161 --> 20:07.597
- Uh-uh, don't do that,

20:07.641 --> 20:09.947
Ms. West Side.

20:09.991 --> 20:11.427
- That is just like a cop.

20:11.471 --> 20:13.386
Always gotta put a label
on somebody.

20:13.429 --> 20:15.605
- Well, obviously sometimes
those labels fit.

20:15.649 --> 20:17.607
- Sometimes they don't.

20:17.651 --> 20:20.784
[smooth music playing
on stereo]

20:20.828 --> 20:22.786
♪

20:22.830 --> 20:24.048
So tell me, Kevin.

20:25.485 --> 20:27.138
- How does a good-looking
brother like you

20:27.182 --> 20:30.577
raise his hand and say,
"I wanna be a cop"--

20:30.620 --> 20:32.187
and in Chicago, no less?

20:32.231 --> 20:35.277
♪

20:35.321 --> 20:37.671
- My pops got locked up early.

20:37.714 --> 20:39.194
And I didn't wanna go out
like that.

20:39.238 --> 20:42.153
So in order to make
a difference,

20:42.197 --> 20:44.068
I decided to do some good
in my community.

20:47.768 --> 20:48.943
- I like that.

20:48.986 --> 20:50.249
- Yeah, that's not too corny
for you?

20:50.292 --> 20:52.163
- No, that's corny as hell.

20:54.035 --> 20:55.166
- But it's honest.

20:55.210 --> 21:02.217
♪

21:06.700 --> 21:08.832
- It's, uh, aspirin.

21:08.876 --> 21:10.225
Mm.

21:10.269 --> 21:12.183
These all-nighters are tough.
- Yeah.

21:12.227 --> 21:14.273
- I'm getting a headache
staring at this monitor.

21:14.316 --> 21:15.665
Guess I'm not as young
as I used to be.

21:15.709 --> 21:17.885
Well, this isn't gonna help.

21:17.928 --> 21:19.321
Decaf.
All they had left.

21:19.365 --> 21:20.975
What's the point?

21:26.850 --> 21:29.026
- Ugh.
- Finally.

21:29.070 --> 21:30.811
- Hey, anybody put eyes
on Nathan?

21:30.854 --> 21:32.726
- No, not yet.

21:32.769 --> 21:35.337
- Well, y'all put a tap
on the wire,

21:35.381 --> 21:37.339
get it out to his peeps.

21:37.383 --> 21:40.037
If anybody knows something
or anything,

21:40.081 --> 21:42.431
you bring his ass down
to the EP, all right?

21:42.475 --> 21:44.520
What'd he say, "EP"?

21:44.564 --> 21:45.956
- That's what I heard too.
- Yeah.

21:46.000 --> 21:47.044
- Let's get a warrant.

21:47.088 --> 21:53.747
♪

22:03.496 --> 22:06.063
- Hey.
- Hey there.

22:06.107 --> 22:08.805
- Yeah, I can dig waking up
to this face.

22:10.024 --> 22:11.852
- Well, look, Kevin.

22:13.114 --> 22:15.725
I had fun and all, but...

22:22.428 --> 22:25.648
- I'm just playing.

22:27.041 --> 22:28.782
- You play too damn rough
for me.

22:28.825 --> 22:32.263
- Mm.
Well, so do you.

22:35.310 --> 22:42.535
♪

22:58.159 --> 23:02.119
♪

23:04.165 --> 23:05.296
I gotta go.

23:05.340 --> 23:06.950
- Mm!
- Mm, I'm sorry.

23:06.994 --> 23:08.604
I gotta go.

23:10.650 --> 23:12.739
- It's okay.

23:12.782 --> 23:14.305
Sort of.

23:15.524 --> 23:17.831
- Listen, let's rain check
round two.

23:17.874 --> 23:22.444
Yeah, you have been
with those white boys too long.

23:22.488 --> 23:23.880
- Well, I could come
to your place

23:23.924 --> 23:25.969
a little bit later,
finish what we started.

23:26.013 --> 23:27.971
♪

23:28.015 --> 23:30.409
- That's better.

23:30.452 --> 23:32.149
And the answer is yes.

23:32.193 --> 23:37.154
♪

23:39.200 --> 23:42.464
♪

23:45.685 --> 23:52.692
♪

23:55.216 --> 23:56.783
- Chicago PD!

23:56.826 --> 23:59.002
Listen up, we have a warrant
to search this establishment.

23:59.046 --> 24:00.656
Hey, hands in the air.
Get 'em where I can see you.

24:00.700 --> 24:03.093
Get 'em up.
Based on what?

24:03.137 --> 24:04.791
- Based on we have a warrant.

24:04.834 --> 24:06.053
Now, everyone get up.

24:06.096 --> 24:07.750
Move with your hands up
against that wall.

24:07.794 --> 24:10.057
- Come on, now.
- Let's go, let's go, let's go.

24:10.100 --> 24:11.188
Come on.

24:14.235 --> 24:21.460
♪

24:42.481 --> 24:46.659
Well, well, well, well,
well, well, well, well.

24:49.009 --> 24:51.011
Oh.

24:52.926 --> 24:54.841
We had to put a rush order
in to ballistics

24:54.884 --> 24:56.146
to go through 'em.

24:56.190 --> 24:57.539
- Oh, if it's too much
trouble...

24:57.583 --> 24:59.759
Your boys can give them back
to the streets.

25:00.890 --> 25:02.675
- Yeah, I'm guessing
there's a good chance

25:02.718 --> 25:06.287
one of them nines is gonna
come back with a body on it...

25:06.330 --> 25:07.636
maybe even Malik's.

25:07.680 --> 25:09.769
- Don't know anybody
named Malik.

25:09.812 --> 25:10.944
- Yeah, you do.

25:10.987 --> 25:12.249
That's the kid you shot
for snitching.

25:12.293 --> 25:13.250
- Doesn't ring a bell.

25:13.294 --> 25:14.643
I'm sorry.

25:14.687 --> 25:17.907
And like I said...
those guns are not mine.

25:17.951 --> 25:19.561
- Then how did they
wind up in your bar?

25:19.605 --> 25:20.997
- Not my bar, neither.

25:21.041 --> 25:23.130
You know...

25:23.173 --> 25:26.176
if you guys are gonna trump up
some fake-ass charges,

25:26.220 --> 25:28.004
go ahead.

25:28.048 --> 25:29.310
Or can I go now?

25:30.224 --> 25:31.617
- You're free to go.

25:33.009 --> 25:34.533
Just don't go too far.

25:37.057 --> 25:38.711
- Yo, Maury.

25:38.754 --> 25:39.973
- Tell me you got
something good.

25:40.016 --> 25:41.452
- Oh, I do.

25:41.496 --> 25:42.932
- No, those are clean,

25:42.976 --> 25:45.674
all of them, but I found
a print on a Beretta 32

25:45.718 --> 25:48.851
that was used in a cold-case
homicide ten years ago.

25:48.895 --> 25:52.072
The handle was wiped clean,
but the magazine wasn't.

25:52.115 --> 25:56.772
I got two partial matches and
then one solid 12-point match.

25:56.816 --> 25:58.774
- 12 points, nice.
You get a hit?

25:58.818 --> 25:59.949
- Yeah.

26:01.560 --> 26:03.474
She's pretty for a killer, huh?

26:03.518 --> 26:08.871
♪

26:16.009 --> 26:16.226
.

26:16.270 --> 26:18.489
- You're late.

26:18.533 --> 26:20.491
It's almost 10:00.
Didn't think you were coming.

26:24.931 --> 26:26.715
Did something happen?

26:26.759 --> 26:28.282
Is it Nathan?
Is he okay?

26:28.325 --> 26:30.284
- Uh, Nathan's fine.

26:30.327 --> 26:32.199
Uh, we're still
trying to track down

26:32.242 --> 26:34.636
his grandma in New Orleans.

26:37.508 --> 26:39.380
You seem preoccupied.

26:41.817 --> 26:44.254
- We found a bag of guns
in Kenny's bar.

26:46.039 --> 26:48.171
One of those guns
was used to kill

26:48.215 --> 26:50.521
a convenience store clerk
ten years ago.

26:52.045 --> 26:55.091
Your prints are on it.

26:56.919 --> 26:58.268
I can explain.

26:58.312 --> 27:00.662
- Listen...

27:00.706 --> 27:03.273
I'm a cop.

27:03.317 --> 27:05.232
You talk to me,
that's evidence.

27:06.189 --> 27:08.888
- Well, I didn't shoot nobody.

27:08.931 --> 27:10.498
Okay?
I swear to God.

27:10.541 --> 27:14.676
Cop or not cop, I'm gonna
tell you what happened,

27:14.720 --> 27:17.853
and you can do what you want.

27:22.728 --> 27:24.817
I was in the car with Kenny.

27:24.860 --> 27:27.297
We were just hanging out,
chilling.

27:27.341 --> 27:30.823
And then he just pulls over
in front of a convenience store

27:30.866 --> 27:33.260
and says that a guy who works
inside owes him some money.

27:33.303 --> 27:35.915
So he hops out and then
he runs into the store.

27:35.958 --> 27:38.265
Two minutes later,

27:38.308 --> 27:40.876
I hear "pop, pop," and then
he hops back in the car,

27:40.920 --> 27:42.138
and we drive off.

27:42.182 --> 27:43.531
I was in the car
the whole time.

27:43.574 --> 27:45.054
I never even stepped foot
in that store.

27:45.098 --> 27:46.752
- How did your prints
get on the magazine?

27:46.795 --> 27:48.797
- 'Cause Kenny told me
to load the damn thing,

27:48.841 --> 27:50.016
so I did it.

27:50.059 --> 27:51.626
I didn't even think about it.

27:51.670 --> 27:54.847
Look, it sounds stupid, okay?
I know.

27:54.890 --> 27:57.371
But I was 17.

27:57.414 --> 27:59.373
I had no idea he was gonna
shoot that guy.

27:59.416 --> 28:00.896
- Doesn't matter
what you think.

28:00.940 --> 28:02.593
♪

28:02.637 --> 28:04.160
You were there.

28:04.204 --> 28:06.946
You were a part of a crime
that resulted in a man's death.

28:06.989 --> 28:09.470
Thinking or not,
naive or not,

28:09.513 --> 28:10.732
that's felony murder.

28:10.776 --> 28:14.562
♪

28:14.605 --> 28:18.914
- I've had a smile on my face
all day

28:18.958 --> 28:20.394
'cause I knew you were
coming here tonight,

28:20.437 --> 28:22.962
and we're sitting here
talking about murder

28:23.005 --> 28:24.311
and fingerprints
and Kenny.

28:24.354 --> 28:25.878
It's just like...
- Laila...

28:25.921 --> 28:27.270
- I'm in a bad dream
or something.

28:27.314 --> 28:28.532
- Laila, this
is the last thing

28:28.576 --> 28:30.491
that I want to be
talking about, okay?

28:30.534 --> 28:31.840
Trust me.

28:31.884 --> 28:33.668
♪

28:33.712 --> 28:34.756
But I don't have a choice.

28:34.800 --> 28:37.628
♪

28:38.934 --> 28:41.937
♪

28:41.981 --> 28:44.592
Are you going to arrest me?

28:44.635 --> 28:45.898
- Come on.

28:45.941 --> 28:49.989
♪

28:52.252 --> 28:53.688
- Like as soon as things
get tough,

28:53.732 --> 28:54.950
you hide behind your badge?

28:54.994 --> 28:57.126
- Don't do that.
Don't put this on me.

28:57.170 --> 28:58.345
I didn't ask for this.

28:58.388 --> 29:00.173
- But it came your way,
nonetheless.

29:00.216 --> 29:02.131
So the question is,
what are you gonna do about it?

29:02.175 --> 29:08.790
♪

29:08.834 --> 29:11.619
I'm not perfect.
I'm not.

29:11.662 --> 29:14.665
Okay?
I made mistakes.

29:14.709 --> 29:16.580
I know that.

29:16.624 --> 29:19.932
But for the past nine years,
I have been a good person.

29:19.975 --> 29:21.411
A very good person.

29:21.455 --> 29:25.154
I've been at
the community center every day,

29:25.198 --> 29:29.115
helping our young people
make good decisions.

29:29.158 --> 29:31.639
♪

29:31.682 --> 29:34.424
The way that I see it...okay,

29:34.468 --> 29:36.383
me being out here
is a good thing.

29:36.426 --> 29:40.604
I'm keeping young brothers
from selling drugs

29:40.648 --> 29:44.870
and joining gangs
and robbing people.

29:44.913 --> 29:46.915
I'm saving lives.

29:46.959 --> 29:49.135
♪

29:49.178 --> 29:53.139
So why arrest me for something
that I did stupid

29:53.182 --> 29:54.662
when I was a kid?

29:57.621 --> 30:02.191
♪

30:02.235 --> 30:03.932
- She was dating Kenny.

30:03.976 --> 30:06.239
Doing what he told her to do.

30:06.282 --> 30:07.718
She stayed right there
in the car.

30:07.762 --> 30:09.764
Said she had no clue
he was gonna pop that dude.

30:09.808 --> 30:13.594
- We got nothing linking
Kenny to Malik's murder.

30:13.637 --> 30:15.857
We gotta use the print.

30:15.901 --> 30:18.904
Force Laila to wear a wire,
get Kenny talking about

30:18.947 --> 30:19.905
how he killed that clerk.

30:21.558 --> 30:22.777
She'd have to do some time.

30:22.821 --> 30:25.345
- I know, but...

30:25.388 --> 30:26.999
we gotta get Kenny
off the street.

30:27.042 --> 30:29.001
♪

30:29.044 --> 30:30.219
- Sarge--
- Let me say something.

30:30.263 --> 30:32.613
The clerk who took two
in the chest,

30:32.656 --> 30:33.744
did he get a free pass?

30:33.788 --> 30:35.485
♪

30:35.529 --> 30:38.532
- That was ten years ago.
- Yeah.

30:38.575 --> 30:42.188
Ten years of hell
for the victim's family.

30:42.231 --> 30:44.233
Waking up every day
thinking about

30:44.277 --> 30:46.018
what happened to their father.

30:46.061 --> 30:48.020
Their husband.
Their son.

30:48.063 --> 30:51.545
♪

30:51.588 --> 30:55.897
Is there something else I need
to know about you and Laila?

30:55.941 --> 31:00.032
♪

31:00.075 --> 31:02.382
- Yeah.

31:02.425 --> 31:04.123
We got together
the other night.

31:04.166 --> 31:06.212
♪

31:06.255 --> 31:09.737
- Then you gotta walk away
from this, Kev.

31:09.780 --> 31:12.000
Now.

31:12.044 --> 31:14.176
Understand?

31:14.220 --> 31:18.006
No more communication
of any kind.

31:18.050 --> 31:25.274
♪

31:28.103 --> 31:29.757
- Okay.

31:31.324 --> 31:35.371
- Help us get Kenny to confess
to murdering that clerk,

31:35.415 --> 31:39.245
agree to testify
to that effect in court,

31:39.288 --> 31:40.942
and you may not do any time.

31:42.117 --> 31:44.946
♪

31:44.990 --> 31:46.252
Kenny's not stupid.

31:46.295 --> 31:48.776
I can't just walk up
to the man and say,

31:48.819 --> 31:50.430
"Hey, remember the night
you murdered that clerk?"

31:50.473 --> 31:54.347
- Laila, I'm trying
to help you, okay?

31:54.390 --> 31:56.740
But to do that,
you gotta help us.

31:56.784 --> 31:58.394
♪

31:58.438 --> 32:00.657
Come on, help us get Kenny
off the street

32:00.701 --> 32:01.615
once and for all.

32:01.658 --> 32:03.051
- Y'all, this is wrong.

32:03.095 --> 32:06.272
And Mr. Undercover too.
He knows this is wrong.

32:06.315 --> 32:09.362
He's just too afraid
to do anything about it.

32:09.405 --> 32:11.930
♪

32:11.973 --> 32:13.844
Where is he anyway?

32:14.889 --> 32:18.632
Is he hiding in the bathroom
like a little punk

32:18.675 --> 32:22.114
- Officer Atwater's
been assigned to another case.

32:22.157 --> 32:27.293
♪

32:27.336 --> 32:29.904
- Of course he has.

32:29.948 --> 32:32.994
'Cause there's nothing left
to do, right?

32:33.038 --> 32:34.953
♪

32:34.996 --> 32:38.695
He got me to help.
Got me into his bed.

32:38.739 --> 32:40.480
♪

32:40.523 --> 32:44.310
And then he buries me for
something I didn't even do.

32:44.353 --> 32:51.578
♪

32:52.405 --> 32:55.843
I saved this punk's life,
and he does this.

32:55.886 --> 32:57.671
♪

32:57.714 --> 32:59.020
For real?

32:59.064 --> 33:01.718
♪

33:01.762 --> 33:04.069
I should have let Kenny know
he was a cop...

33:04.112 --> 33:07.681
♪

33:07.724 --> 33:10.118
And let him kill his ass.

33:10.162 --> 33:17.386
♪

33:22.087 --> 33:22.304
.

33:28.919 --> 33:30.965
- Yeah, we got some equipment
to load.

33:39.234 --> 33:41.932
- There's really nothing
I can say,

33:41.976 --> 33:44.500
other than I'm sorry.

33:44.544 --> 33:46.024
I didn't want
for this to happen.

33:46.067 --> 33:48.417
- But you didn't do anything
to stop it, either.

33:51.594 --> 33:53.335
- It's not that easy, Laila.

33:53.379 --> 33:55.076
- You're right.

33:55.120 --> 33:58.775
It required you
to have some courage.

34:02.083 --> 34:03.041
- You don't understand--

34:03.084 --> 34:04.912
- No, sure, I do.

34:06.218 --> 34:09.960
You one of those brothers
that like to straddle the line.

34:10.004 --> 34:11.875
You pick and choose
when to be black

34:11.919 --> 34:13.442
and when to be blue.

34:15.096 --> 34:15.836
- Mm-mm.

34:15.879 --> 34:17.881
Hmm?

34:17.925 --> 34:19.274
You gonna screw him over too?

34:19.318 --> 34:20.971
Is that your thing?
Is that what you do?

34:21.015 --> 34:22.538
You screw over your own kind?

34:32.070 --> 34:33.810
- Yo, Nathan.
Come on, man.

34:33.854 --> 34:35.160
Found your grandma.
She can't wait to see you.

34:35.203 --> 34:36.683
Let's get up out of here.
Come on.

34:36.726 --> 34:38.424
- No, man.
I ain't leaving.

34:38.467 --> 34:39.903
♪

34:39.947 --> 34:41.644
- We already talked about this.

34:41.688 --> 34:43.820
- Can't go.
I need to stay here.

34:43.864 --> 34:44.995
Help my aunt.

34:46.780 --> 34:50.523
- Kenny's people broke into
my aunt's house last night.

34:50.566 --> 34:52.438
Tore it apart, wrote all kinds
of nasty things on the walls.

34:52.481 --> 34:54.004
- Okay, well, I'll send
somebody over there

34:54.048 --> 34:55.136
to check on her,
but you gotta get

34:55.180 --> 34:56.616
your ass up out of here, man.

34:56.659 --> 34:58.879
- Man, wherever I go,
Kenny's gonna track me down.

34:58.922 --> 35:01.577
Okay, so I might as well
just stay here.

35:01.621 --> 35:03.144
- You're a boy.
All right?

35:03.188 --> 35:04.798
That means that you can
go to another city

35:04.841 --> 35:06.016
and start all over.

35:06.060 --> 35:07.279
- I can take care of myself.

35:07.322 --> 35:09.237
Look, dude,
I'm not going nowhere.

35:09.281 --> 35:11.805
All right? So you might as well
just--just lock me up

35:11.848 --> 35:13.589
or just let me go.

35:13.633 --> 35:15.591
♪

35:15.635 --> 35:16.636
- If that's what you want.

35:16.679 --> 35:23.947
♪

35:26.950 --> 35:28.430
- Hey, all right,
look at me.

35:28.474 --> 35:30.737
The distress word is "Voight."
- Mm-hmm.

35:30.780 --> 35:32.565
- If anything goes bad,
just say the word,

35:32.608 --> 35:33.566
and we'll bust in.

35:33.609 --> 35:35.176
- I got it.

35:35.220 --> 35:37.309
- All you gotta do is get Kenny
to incriminate himself, okay?

35:37.352 --> 35:38.962
Just get him talking
about the robberies--

35:39.006 --> 35:40.964
- I said I got it.

35:43.837 --> 35:46.448
All right.
Go, go, go, go, go.

35:49.495 --> 35:56.502
♪

36:02.247 --> 36:04.205
- Hey, you.
Where Kenny?

36:04.249 --> 36:06.033
- Hey, girl.
Don't know.

36:06.076 --> 36:07.643
Check the back office.

36:07.687 --> 36:09.210
- Just play it cool.

36:12.648 --> 36:14.520
Oh, God.

36:14.563 --> 36:16.826
Voight! Voight!

36:19.089 --> 36:20.308
Voight!
- Laila.

36:20.352 --> 36:21.918
- Police.
Put your hands on the bar.

36:21.962 --> 36:23.572
Don't move.
Put your hands on the bar.

36:24.660 --> 36:26.532
- Laila.

36:28.055 --> 36:30.231
It's all right.
What happened?

36:30.275 --> 36:31.972
- I don't know what happened.

36:32.015 --> 36:33.669
He was like that
when I walked in.

36:33.713 --> 36:35.018
- All right.
It's okay.

36:37.499 --> 36:39.458
- It's okay.

36:39.501 --> 36:40.850
- He's cold.

36:40.894 --> 36:42.417
- Come on.

36:42.461 --> 36:45.855
♪

36:47.248 --> 36:48.597
- Yeah, she's all right.

36:48.641 --> 36:50.251
Tech said Kenny's been dead
for three hours.

36:50.295 --> 36:52.384
- Bartender claims
he didn't see anything.

36:53.863 --> 36:55.387
- No, but I'm guessing
there's a lot of contenders.

36:56.953 --> 36:58.955
- Just two nine-millimeter
shell casings on the floor.

36:58.999 --> 37:00.783
That's about it.
- That's not our problem.

37:00.827 --> 37:04.134
Homicide's taking the case,
so pack up any loose ends.

37:04.178 --> 37:05.353
Let's get out of here.
- Copy that.

37:05.397 --> 37:06.572
- Wait, Kev.

37:06.615 --> 37:08.226
Hang on a sec.

37:10.271 --> 37:11.490
What's up?

37:12.708 --> 37:14.232
Excuse me?

37:15.929 --> 37:18.453
You gotta be kidding me.

37:18.497 --> 37:19.889
What?
No.

37:19.933 --> 37:23.241
Listen, there is always
something you can do about it.

37:23.284 --> 37:26.722
Let me tell you something,
next time you need a favor,

37:26.766 --> 37:28.768
don't bother asking me.

37:28.811 --> 37:32.032
Yeah.
I gotta go.

37:35.078 --> 37:40.258
♪

37:40.301 --> 37:43.391
Kevin...

37:43.435 --> 37:44.914
it's the ASA...

37:47.961 --> 37:55.185
♪

38:03.498 --> 38:07.502
Look, with Kenny dead,
there is no trial.

38:09.156 --> 38:13.029
The ASA is not willing
to be as...

38:13.073 --> 38:15.554
as lenient.

38:18.687 --> 38:20.689
- It's gonna be three years.

38:20.733 --> 38:22.952
♪

38:22.996 --> 38:25.825
Said that's the best
they can do.

38:25.868 --> 38:27.479
I'm sorry.

38:27.522 --> 38:28.828
Jenna.

38:28.871 --> 38:36.139
♪

39:05.517 --> 39:12.567
♪

39:18.704 --> 39:20.227
- Kenny's dead.

39:23.273 --> 39:26.189
- He killed Malik
for no reason.

39:26.233 --> 39:28.453
And he was gonna
kill me too, so--

39:28.496 --> 39:30.280
so I did what I had to do.

39:30.324 --> 39:36.896
♪

39:36.939 --> 39:39.768
- Give me the gun.

39:39.812 --> 39:47.080
♪

40:01.181 --> 40:02.878
- So what,
you gonna arrest me now?

40:02.922 --> 40:10.190
♪

40:27.903 --> 40:35.128
♪

40:57.977 --> 41:05.201
♪
